<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="279" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,918,2025]" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,990,1016]" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be recognized by the following combination of characters: mandible with two teeth (
<figureCitation box="[222,310,1027,1053]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,349,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-69@15.[151,1435,345,1837]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Details of Forrestopius yungas, sp. nov. A. Habitus of female, in lateral view (scale bar = 1 mm) B. Pronotum, in lateral view C. Facial view D. Head in frontolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531267" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531267/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
), antenna with 19 flagellomeres, scape predominantly yellowish brown, face and clypeus forming a continuous surface, pronotum with dorso-posterior corner yellowish brown, and propodeum with lateromedian and lateral longitudinal carinae. It can be differentiated from other species of the genus by having several wrinkles arising from pronotal pit with their upper ends reaching almost the anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1051,1140,1135,1161]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,349,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-69@15.[151,1435,345,1837]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Details of Forrestopius yungas, sp. nov. A. Habitus of female, in lateral view (scale bar = 1 mm) B. Pronotum, in lateral view C. Facial view D. Head in frontolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531267" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531267/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="280" pageId="14" pageNumber="279" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,918,2025]" box="[199,991,1170,1197]" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,448,1170,1197]" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Description. Female:</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[600,689,1171,1197]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.9" pageId="14" pageNumber="279" unit="mm" value="6.9">6.9 mm</quantity>
. Fore wing length 
<quantity box="[898,987,1170,1197]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="279" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,918,2025]" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis box="[199,267,1207,1233]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Head.</emphasis>
Face and clypeus forming a continuous surface, 0.9× as long as wide, smooth with punctures with upper half slightly striate (
<figureCitation box="[380,469,1243,1269]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,349,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-69@15.[151,1435,345,1837]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Details of Forrestopius yungas, sp. nov. A. Habitus of female, in lateral view (scale bar = 1 mm) B. Pronotum, in lateral view C. Facial view D. Head in frontolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531267" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531267/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
); labrum not exposed when mandibles closed; mandibles with two teeth; malar space 1.0× as long as basal mandibular width; lateral ocellus separated from compound eye by about 1.1× maximum ocellar diameter; distance between ocelli 1.0× maximum ocellar diameter; vertex behind ocellar triangle slightly declivous, occiput concave; gena in lateral view 0.8× as long as compound eye; antenna with 19 flagellomeres, ratio of length from second to fourth flagellomeres: 0.9:0.9:0.9, subapical flagellomere 1.0× as long as centrally broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,918,2025]" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis box="[199,327,1423,1448]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">
<taxonomicName box="[199,322,1423,1448]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="14" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesosoma</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Pronotum with several wrinkles from pronotal pit, upper end almost reaching to anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[160,249,1459,1485]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,349,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-69@15.[151,1435,345,1837]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Details of Forrestopius yungas, sp. nov. A. Habitus of female, in lateral view (scale bar = 1 mm) B. Pronotum, in lateral view C. Facial view D. Head in frontolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531267" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531267/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
); metapleuron polished with isolated setae, posteroventrally smooth; submetapleural carina scrobiculate, anteriorly expanded into conspicuous triangular lobe. Propodeum with lateromedian longitudinal carina strong, slightly closer to each other anteriorly; lateral longitudinal carina complete; posterior transverse carina present; area superomedia 2.6× as long as wide. Fore wing with vein 
<emphasis box="[844,877,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Cu</emphasis>
1 
<emphasis box="[891,905,1567,1592]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">a</emphasis>
between 
<emphasis box="[1014,1047,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Cu</emphasis>
1 
<emphasis box="[1061,1075,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">b</emphasis>
and 2 
<emphasis box="[1146,1202,1567,1592]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">m-cu</emphasis>
2.3× as long as 
<emphasis box="[1390,1423,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Cu</emphasis>
1 between 
<emphasis box="[252,280,1603,1628]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Rs</emphasis>
&amp; 
<emphasis box="[302,325,1603,1628]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">M</emphasis>
and 1 
<emphasis box="[396,452,1603,1628]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">m-cu</emphasis>
; 2 
<emphasis box="[482,533,1603,1628]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">rs-m</emphasis>
1.0× as long as abscissa of 
<emphasis box="[851,874,1603,1628]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">M</emphasis>
between 2 
<emphasis box="[997,1048,1603,1628]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">rs-m</emphasis>
and 2 
<emphasis box="[1119,1175,1603,1628]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">m-cu</emphasis>
. Hind wing with distal abscissa of 
<emphasis box="[282,305,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">M</emphasis>
indistinguishable, distal abscissa of 
<emphasis box="[719,752,1639,1665]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Cu</emphasis>
1 and 1 
<emphasis box="[835,852,1639,1665]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">A</emphasis>
sclerotized throughout. Outer metatibial spurs 0.8× as long as inner spur.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,918,2025]" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis box="[199,323,1711,1736]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Metasoma.</emphasis>
Tergite I 1.3× as long as posteriorly wide, lateromedian carina extending 0.3× length of tergite; tergite II 1.0× as long as posteriorly wide; laterotergite II 0.1× as wide as long; laterotergite III 0.5× as wide as long, wedge-shaped, mesal edge straight.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,918,2025]" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis box="[199,283,1819,1845]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="279">Colour.</emphasis>
Head extensively black except mouth parts and scape yellowish brown; pedicel and flagellomeres brown. 
<taxonomicName box="[237,358,1855,1881]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="14" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mesosoma</taxonomicName>
except dorso-posterior corner of pronotum yellowish brown and tegula yellowish; fore and mid legs testaceous, femur ventrally and tibia dorsally off-white; hind leg pale yellow, coxa black gradually changing to brown dorsally, trochanter, trochantellus, basal third of femur, distal 1/3 of tibia and tarsomeres light brown. Metasomal tergites dark brown with soft metallic blue reflection, metasomal tergites II–V distal margin and laterotergites brownish; valvae testaceous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,321]" box="[199,386,151,177]" pageId="15" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,269,151,177]" pageId="15" pageNumber="280">Male:</emphasis>
Unknown
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="280" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,321]" pageId="15" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,187,213]" pageId="15" pageNumber="280">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was collected in a wet forest, in 
<collectingCountry box="[820,871,187,213]" name="Peru" pageId="15" pageNumber="280">Peru</collectingCountry>
at 
<quantity box="[904,982,186,213]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.52" pageId="15" pageNumber="280" unit="m" value="1520.0">1520m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[996,1098,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,881,905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,857]" captionTargetId="figure-23@16.[151,1436,181,858]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Geographic distribution of the Forrestopius species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531269/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="280">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
). It occurs in the same locality as 
<taxonomicName authority="Alvarado &amp; Palacio, 2021" authorityName="Alvarado &amp; Palacio" authorityYear="2021" box="[182,309,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="runasimi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[182,309,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="280">F. runasimi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[316,405,223,249]" pageId="15" pageNumber="280">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[316,405,223,249]" pageId="15" pageNumber="280" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="280" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,321]" pageId="15" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,259,285]" pageId="15" pageNumber="280">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alvarado &amp; Palacio" authorityYear="2021" box="[574,653,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yungas">
<emphasis box="[574,653,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="280">yungas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in honor of the Yungas stretch of forest along the eastern slope of the Andes Mountains.
</paragraph>
